  <h2>Summary</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>40°F (4°C) won’t cause frost damage, but warm-season seedlings can stall.</li>
    <li>Cool-season seedlings usually tolerate 40°F (4°C) without long-term issues.</li>
    <li>Use covers and shelter if plants are already outside.</li>
  </ol>

